, _jsx(Heading, {\n      level: \"2\",\n      id: \"what-is-a-runtime%3F\",\n      children: \"What is a runtime?\"\n    }), \"\\n\", _jsxs(_components.p, {\n      children: [\"JavaScript (or, more formally, ECMAScript) is just a \", _jsx(_components.em, {\n        children: \"specification\"\n      }), \" for a programming language. Anyone can write a JavaScript \", _jsx(_components.em, {\n        children: \"engine\"\n      }), \" that ingests a valid JavaScript program and executes it. The two most popular engines in use today are V8 (developed by Google)\\nand JavaScriptCore (developed by Apple). Both are open source.\"]\n    }), \"\\n\", _jsxs(_components.p, {\n      children: [\"But most JavaScript programs don’t run in a vacuum. They need a way to access the outside world to perform useful tasks. This is where \", _jsx(_components.em, {\n        children: \"runtimes\"\n      }), \" come in. They implement additional APIs that are then made available to the JavaScript programs they execute.\"]\n    }), \"\\n\", _jsx(Heading, {\n      level: \"3\",\n      id: \"browsers\",\n      children: \"Browsers\"\n    }), \"\\n\", _jsxs(_components.p, {\n      children: [\"Notably, browsers ship with JavaScript runtimes that implement a set of Web-specific APIs that are exposed via the global \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n        children: \"window\"\n      }), \" object. Any JavaScript code executed by the browser can use these APIs to implement interactive or dynamic behavior in the context of the current webpage.\"]\n    }), \"\\n\", _jsx(Heading, {\n      level: \"3\",\n      id: \"node-js\",\n      children: \"Node.js\"\n    }), \"\\n\", _jsxs(_components.p, {\n      children: [\"Similarly, Node.js is a JavaScript runtime that can be used in non-browser environments, like servers. JavaScript programs executed by Node.js have access to a set of Node.js-specific \", _jsx(_components.a, {\n        href: \"https://nodejs.org/api/globals.html\",\n        children: \"globals\"\n      }), \" like \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n        children: \"Buffer\"\n      }), \", \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n        children: \"process\"\n      }), \", and \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n        children: \"__dirname\"\n      }), \" in addition to built-in modules for performing OS-level tasks like reading/writing files (\", _jsx(_components.code, {\n        children: \"node:fs\"\n      }), \") and networking (\", _jsx(_components.code, {\n        children: \"node:net\"\n      }), \", \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n        children: \"node:http\"\n      }), \"). Node.js also implements a CommonJS-based module system and resolution algorithm that pre-dates JavaScript’s native module system.\"]\n    }), \"\\n\", _jsx(_components.p, {\n      children: \"Bun is designed as a faster, leaner, more modern replacement for Node.js.\"\n    }), \"\\n\", _jsx(Heading, {\n      level: \"2\",\n      id: \"design-goals\",\n      children: \"Design goals\"\n    }), \"\\n\", _jsx(_components.p, {\n      children: \"Bun is designed from the ground-up with today’s JavaScript ecosystem in mind.\"\n    }), \"\\n\", _jsxs(_components.ul, {\n      children: [\"\\n\", _jsxs(_components.li, {\n        children: [_jsx(_components.strong, {\n          children: \"Speed\"\n        }), \". Bun processes start \", _jsx(_components.a, {\n          href: \"https://twitter.com/jarredsumner/status/1499225725492076544\",\n          children: \"4x faster than Node.js\"\n        }), \" currently (try it yourself!)\"]\n      }), \"\\n\", _jsxs(_components.li, {\n        children: [_jsx(_components.strong, {\n          children: \"TypeScript \u0026 JSX support\"\n        }), \". You can directly execute \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n          children: \".jsx\"\n        }), \", \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n          children: \".ts\"\n        }), \", and \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n          children: \".tsx\"\n        }), \" files; Bun’s transpiler converts these to vanilla JavaScript before execution.\"]\n      }), \"\\n\", _jsxs(_components.li, {\n        children: [_jsx(_components.strong, {\n          children: \"ESM \u0026 CommonJS compatibility\"\n        }), \". The world is moving towards ES modules (ESM), but millions of packages on npm still require CommonJS. Bun recommends ES modules, but supports CommonJS.\"]\n      }), \"\\n\", _jsxs(_components.li, {\n        children: [_jsx(_components.strong, {\n          children: \"Web-standard APIs\"\n        }), \". Bun implements standard Web APIs like \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n          children: \"fetch\"\n        }), \", \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n          children: \"WebSocket\"\n        }), \", and \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n          children: \"ReadableStream\"\n        }), \". Bun is powered by the JavaScriptCore engine, which is developed by Apple for Safari, so some APIs like \", _jsx(_components.a, {\n          href: \"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Headers\",\n          children: _jsx(_components.code, {\n            children: \"Headers\"\n          })\n        }), \" and \", _jsx(_components.a, {\n          href: \"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/URL\",\n          children: _jsx(_components.code, {\n            children: \"URL\"\n          })\n        }), \" directly use \", _jsx(_components.a, {\n          href: \"https://github.com/oven-sh/bun/blob/HEAD/src/bun.js/bindings/webcore/JSFetchHeaders.cpp\",\n          children: \"Safari’s implementation\"\n        }), \".\"]\n      }), \"\\n\", _jsxs(_components.li, {\n        children: [_jsx(_components.strong, {\n          children: \"Node.js compatibility\"\n        }), \". In addition to supporting Node-style module resolution, Bun aims for full compatibility with built-in Node.js globals (\", _jsx(_components.code, {\n          children: \"process\"\n        }), \", \", _jsx(_components.code, {\n          children: \"Buffer\"\n        }), \") and modules (\", _jsx(_components.co